==== 批评 ====

根据《[[卫报|卫报]]》的试图与特拉斯接触的批评家{{le|乔治·莫比奥特|George Monbiot}}的说法，<ref name="Monbiot">{{cite news|last1=Monbiot|first1=George|title=Toothless Environment Agency is allowing the living world to be wrecked with impunity|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/georgemonbiot/2015/nov/12/toothless-environment-agency-is-allowing-the-living-world-to-be-wrecked-with-impunity|accessdate=2015-11-13|work=The Guardian|date=2015-11-12|archive-date=2021-02-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210214010903/https://www.theguardian.com/environment/georgemonbiot/2015/nov/12/toothless-environment-agency-is-allowing-the-living-world-to-be-wrecked-with-impunity|dead-url=no}}</ref>特拉斯是“坚定的执著于一套世界应该是什么样的理论，对于各种论据、事实或经验无动于衷。在最近的支出审查中，她是第一位冒着丢官的风险自愿大幅裁减本部门经费的大臣。她似乎决心拆除保护我们生活质量的防护网：保卫我们所爱的地方和野生动物的规则和机构。”<ref name="Monbiot"/>

=== 司法大臣 ===

在2016年7月14日，[[德蕾莎·梅伊|德蕾莎·梅伊]]任命特拉斯为[[特蕾莎·梅内阁|内阁]][[司法大臣_(英国)|司法大臣]]兼[[大法官_(英國)|大法官]]。特拉斯成为历史上第一位担任这一职务的女性。这一任命引来[[英国司法部|司法副大臣]][[爱德华·福克斯|爱德华·福克斯]]的批评，他随即从政府辞职，并质疑特拉斯能否在首相需要的时候发挥影响力代表法官群体。<ref>{{cite news |last=Gibb |first=Frances |title=Justice minister quits with blast at ‘novice’ lord chancellor |url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/justice-minister-quits-with-blast-at-novice-lord-chancellor-x99qd8xl5 |date=2016-07-19 |accessdate=2016-07-19 |newspaper=[[The_Times|The Times]] |subscription=y |archive-date=2019-05-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190517043900/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/justice-minister-quits-with-blast-at-novice-lord-chancellor-x99qd8xl5 |dead-url=no }}</ref>特拉斯自己说，福克斯在公开批评之前没有和自己联系，自己从来没有见过他，也没有和他说话。<ref>[http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/01/legal-firms-pursuing-troops-is-outrageous-says-liz-truss/ "Legal firms pursuing troops is outrageous, says Liz Truss"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/01/legal-firms-pursuing-troops-is-outrageous-says-liz-truss/ |date=20201106130120 }}, Telegraph, 1 October 2016</ref>

在“英国脱欧”第50条案中，由于没有更有力地支持司法机构和司法独立原则，特拉斯受到严重的批评，包括前{{le|总检察长|Attorney General for England and Wales}}[[多米尼克·葛里夫|多米尼克·葛里夫]]和刑事律师协会，分区法院的三名法官因为对政府的裁决受到政治家和新闻界的口诛笔伐。<ref>{{Cite web |title= Unrepentant Mail demands 'public hearings' for judges as Brexit row escalates |url= https://www.lawgazette.co.uk/law/unrepentant-mail-demands-public-hearings-for-judges-as-brexit-row-escalates/5058689.article |website= Law Society Gazette |date= 2016-11-07 |accessdate= 2016-11-09 |archive-date= 2020-10-24 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201024151546/https://www.lawgazette.co.uk/law/unrepentant-mail-demands-public-hearings-for-judges-as-brexit-row-escalates/5058689.article |dead-url= no }}</ref>前大法官{{le|查尔斯·福尔克纳|Charlie Falconer, Baron Falconer of Thoroton}}曾经指出，<ref>{{Cite web |author= Charles Falconer |date= 2016-07-25 |title= This row over Liz Truss as Lord Chancellor isn't about gender. Its about the law |url= https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2016/jul/25/row-over-liz-truss-sexism-gender-law-lord-chancellor |website= [[theguardian.com|theguardian.com]] |accessdate= 2017-04-12 |archive-date= 2020-11-08 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201108101155/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2016/jul/25/row-over-liz-truss-sexism-gender-law-lord-chancellor |dead-url= no }}</ref>像她前任[[克里斯·葛瑞林|克里斯·葛瑞林]]和[[麥可·戈夫|迈克尔·戈夫]]一样，她缺乏宪法所要求的基本法律专门知识，要求解任她的司法大臣一职，因为她在“向法官表示他们失去了宪法保护者的角色”这一件事上反应不足。

特拉斯否认她没有捍卫法官。“独立的司法机构是[[法治|法治]]的基石，对我们的宪法和自由至关重要，”她写道。“我担任司法大臣就会承担维护司法独立的责任。我就职时的誓言要求我这样做。我非常认真对待，我会一直这样做的。”<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/nov/10/liz-truss-rebuffs-criticism-over-newspaper-attacks-on-brexit-judges/ "Liz Truss rebuffs criticism over newspaper attacks on Brexit judges"] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/nov/10/liz-truss-rebuffs-criticism-over-newspaper-attacks-on-brexit-judges/ |date=20201108120027 }}, Guardian, 10 November 2016</ref>她还表示，独立的司法机构足以抵御《每日电讯报》和《每日邮报》的袭击。<ref>[http://www.thetimes.co.uk/edition/comment/the-bulging-intray-facing-president-trump-62rxh35gs/ "The bulging intray facing President Trump"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/edition/comment/the-bulging-intray-facing-president-trump-62rxh35gs/ |date=20200108181058 }}, The Times, 10 November 2016</ref>然而，在2017年三月，[[英格兰及威尔士首席法官|英格兰及威尔士首席法官]][[约翰·托马斯|约翰·托马斯]]告诉上院宪制事务专责委员会，特拉斯是完全错误的，因为她不能批评媒体，托马斯补充说：“我可以理解11月份的压力如何，但她已经采取了宪法上绝对错误的立场 - {{le|巡回法官|Circuit judge (England and Wales)}}非常关心。我的同事们写信给了大法官，因为诉讼当事人来了，说‘你’是人民的敌人 - 我不认为我们[法官]受到保护是绝对必要的，因为我们只遵照我们的誓言，而不担心或受制于物议。”

随着2015年和2016年监狱暴力事件的大幅增加，<ref name="guardian-20161027">{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2016/oct/27/prison-violence-staff-cuts-moj-deaths-assaults |title=Prison violence epidemic partly due to staff cuts, MoJ admits |author=Alan Travis |newspaper=The Guardian |date=2016-10-27 |accessdate=2016-11-17 |archive-date=2019-04-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416160213/https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2016/oct/27/prison-violence-staff-cuts-moj-deaths-assaults |dead-url=no }}</ref>特拉斯宣布，2016年11月，{{le|监狱系统|Her Majesty's Prison Service}}会获得一项13亿英镑的投资计划，并招募了2,500名附加监狱官，部分扭转了以前[[第一次戴维·卡梅伦内阁|联合政府]]的削减。<ref name="bbc-20161103">{{cite news |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-37854358 |title=Prisons to get 'biggest overhaul in a generation' |work=BBC News |date=2016-11-03 |accessdate=2016-11-17 |archive-date=2020-11-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108124216/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-37854358 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="guardian-20161103">{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2016/nov/02/prisons-in-england-and-wales-given-boost-of-2500-new-staff-to-tackle-violence |title=Prisons in England and Wales to get 2,500 extra staff to tackle violence |author=Alan Travis |newspaper=The Guardian |date=2016-11-03 |accessdate=2016-11-17 |archive-date=2019-09-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190930015219/https://www.theguardian.com/society/2016/nov/02/prisons-in-england-and-wales-given-boost-of-2500-new-staff-to-tackle-violence |dead-url=no }}</ref>

